review_blob: Nice oaky aroma, slightly bitter but not so much.  Kind of a coffee and nut flavor, very tasty.  This is a beer I enjoy thoroughly.  Should really only be consumed warm, though.  Would like to try it on tap someday.
Its a classic, readily available and goes well with anything.  Lighter than what Im used to with brown ale, but good nonetheless.  Good flavor, great color, and doesnt leave anything nasty behind.

Was suprised by the flavor of this one.  Wasnt expecting the fruity, herbal taste that I got.  If you can forget the grainy aftertaste, Its pretty decent as far as golden ales go (not really a type of beer Im crazy about.)  Id drink another one.
beer_name: Flying Dog Tire Bite Golden Ale

review_blob: Probably my first really dedicated type of beer, being a Southern girl at heart.  You cant beat a Pabst - good and cheap.
